|GKB-- Return to Earth ------------------------------------------|000

Invocation: |CKBreturn to earth|000
Command:    |CKBreclaim [corpse]|000
Aliases:    |CKBreturnearth|000, |CKBcompost|000
Current:    Tellurian

Return to Earth lets a Druid kneel beside a fallen creature and
return its body to the living soil.  The corpse is removed, but any
items or reagents inside it fall into the room first.

The rite restores nwyfre based on the moons that are present.  Dailos
feeds Daloan, Markas feeds Marken, and Tekal feeds Tekali.  Fuller
phases return more, while crescent phases return less.  If no moon is
visible, the corpse returns to the earth as Tellurian nwyfre instead.

Larger, stronger, and less-harvested corpses return more to the cycle.
A corpse that has already been skinned, gutted, deboned, decapitated,
or stripped of teeth still works, but gives less.

Training Return to Earth makes the rite more efficient.  As your
mastery improves, the invocation costs less Tellurian nwyfre to begin,
returns more nwyfre from each corpse, and can draw a larger offering
before reaching your current's natural limit.

If you perform the invocation at your own Sacred Grove, the grove also
deepens from the offering.  Training the invocation increases this
grove growth as well.

Player corpses are never consumed by this invocation.
